</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-EQUITIES-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EQUITIES 
</HEADLINE>
  (lb) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The following equity and convertible debt offerings are expected
this week:
</P>
<P>
   American Bank Note Holographics Inc., Elmsford, N.Y., an initial
public offering of 13.6 million shares. NMS.
</P>
<P>
   Aptargroup Inc., Crystal Lake, Ill., 1.7 million shares.
Goldman, Sachs &AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
   Broadcast.com Inc., Dallas, an initial public offering of 2.5
million shares. Morgan Stanley Dean Witter.
</P>
<P>
   Cost-U-Less Inc., Bellevue, Wash., an initial public offering of
1.6 million shares. Cruttenden Roth Inc.
</P>
<P>
   Esenjay Exploration Inc., Corpus Christi, Texas, 5 million
shares. Gaines Berland Inc.
</P>
<P>
   Firstlink Communications Inc., Portland, Ore., an initial public
offering of 1.4 million units, each consisting of one common share
and one warrant. Kashner Davidson Securities Corp.
</P>
<P>
   Genvec Inc., Rockville, Md., an initial public offering of 2.5
million shares. BancAmerica Robertson Stephens.
</P>
<P>
   Interactive Magic Inc., Morrisville, N.C., an initial public
offering of 2.8 million shares. Bluestone Capital.
</P>
<P>
   National Equipment Service Inc., Evanston, Ill., an initial
public offering of 6 million shares. Salomon Smith Barney.
</P>
