   BRITISHOPEN-PARNEVIK _ In the game of life, Jesper Parnevik has
never aimed for the center of the fairway. Here's a guy who
believes in reincarnation, eats volcanic dust to cleanse his
system, has had his blood analyzed by radiation, uses stroboscopic
glasses, meditates as the sun rises over his South Palm Beach home,
has had his metal fillings replaced with ceramic ones to reduce
mercury levels and once drove to the wrong city for a tournament.
Lately, Parnevik has had another odd habit of almost winning the
British Open, which starts Thursday at Royal Birkdale. (Dolch, Palm
Beach Post)
