<HEADLINE>
KING DUCKS ANOTHER PUNCH
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
corrects spelling of Kevin Kelley; result of Nelson-Leija fight 
By MICHAEL ROSENTHAL  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ This and that from the boxing world:
</P>
<P>
   Well, we haven't seen the last of promoter Don King.
</P>
<P>
   King, the ``Only in America'' man, has again ended up on the
fortunate end of the American justice system. He was acquitted last
week on all charges that he faked a contract to cheat Lloyd's of
London out of $350,000 after one of his boxing promotions was
canceled in 1991.
</P>
<P>
   Other examples of his good fortune:
</P>
<P>
   In 1954, he shot and killed a man, but it was ruled justifiable
homicide.
</P>
<P>
   In 1967, he was convicted of second-degree murder, but the
charge was reduced to manslaughter. He served only 3 years, 11
months in an Ohio prison.
</P>
<P>
   In 1984, King was named in a 23-count indictment for income-tax
evasion but was acquitted of all counts the following year.
</P>
<P>
   And, finally, there was last week's decision,
</P>
<P>
   It'll be interesting to see what role King will play now.
</P>
<P>
   He's 65 and reported to be in failing health. He lost his gold
mine, Mike Tyson. Evander Holyfield is his only fighter with the
ability to generate a great deal of money and it's unclear how many
fights under which he has the champ under contract.
</P>
<P>
   Somehow, it seems, he'll make his presence felt....
</P>
<P>
   Most people in the boxing world have respect for the skills of
Naseem Hamed, the flamboyant Briton who has become one of the
sport's biggest moneymakers.
</P>
<P>
   One of the most-respected trainers in the world isn't one of
them.
</P>
<P>
   Emanuel Steward laid into the unbeaten featherweight.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's strictly hype,'' Steward said. ``They have to match him
very carefully. He can't fight. That's why they're matching him
with weather-worn fighters. He can't beat the top fighters.
</P>
<P>
   ``...He doesn't have the basic foundation (of skills). They put
him in with older guys (example: 30-year-old Kevin Kelley) and he
beats them with the physical strength of a young man.''
</P>
<P>
   What do you (ITAL)really(END ITAL) think, Emanuel?...
</P>
<P>
   Long-time broadcaster, Don Dunphy, who recently turned 90,
worked more than 2,000 fights, including roughly 200 championship
bouts, according to the New York Times.
</P>
<P>
   He believes Joe Louis' knockout of Billy Conn in 1941 was the
most dramatic moment in the sport.
</P>
<P>
   However, who's the best he's seen?
</P>
<P>
   ``Louis, Marciano and Ali were, to me, the best of the
heavyweights,'' he wrote in his 1988 autobiography, ``but Robinson
was unquestionably the best of three divisions _ lightweight,
welterweight and middleweight _ and he was winning the
light-heavyweight title (from Joey Maxim at Yankee Stadium) when
the 106-degree heat did him in.
</P>
<P>
   ``I agree with those who say that Sugar Ray Robinson was the
greatest.''...
</P>
<P>
   Dan Goossen, the promoter of Azumah Nelson, is trying to match
his fighter against Hamed.
</P>
<P>
   Nelson, who stopped Jesse James Leija on Saturday, has a
terrific chin. Without question, Hamed's power would be tested.
However, he and his handlers know that and it might be difficult to
make the fight....
</P>
<P>
   Lou Del Valle told a group of writers that his ``fantasy is to
tell all you guys, `Kneel, kneel. Bow your heads,''' after he beats
Roy Jones Jr. on Saturday at The Theater at Madison Square Garden.
</P>
<P>
   If they bow their heads, it will be to get a better look at Del
Valle lying on the canvas in the title-unification fight on HBO.
</P>
<P>
   This should be a typical one-sided Jones victory. Only a master
boxer _ like Montell Griffin _ could give Jones problems. Del
Valle, while capable, is hardly that fighter.
</P>
<P>
   His only loss, on points, came against Virgil Hill in 1996.
Jones knocked out Hill in four rounds with a crushing body punch
earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
   If Jones doesn't attack aggressively, this could be a dull
fight. Both fighters are counterpunchers.
</P>
<P>
   On the same card, Kevin Kelley faces Derrick Gainer in a
junior-lightweight rematch of a wonderful fight in 1996, in which
Kelley, his eye swollen shut and behind on points, stopped Gainer
with one punch in the eighth round....
</P>
<P>
   A bout between Jorge Paez and Gustavo Cuello on July 25 in Las
Vegas has been rescheduled for Aug. 22 because Paez had oral
surgery.
</P>
<P>
   Paez, too, is campaigning for a shot at Hamed. Wouldn't that be
interesting? ``The Clown Prince'' and ``The Prince.''...
</P>
<P>
   The Forum has announced the pairings for its junior-lightweight
tournament. On July 27, Jose Luis Castillo will face unbeaten Adan
Castillas and Ricard Rivera will take on Armando Bosques. On Aug.
17, undefeated Acelino Freitas (15-0, 14 KOs) fights Vincent Howard
and Sandro Marcos faces Golden ``Demon'' Johnson....
</P>
<P>
   The Forum's Ed Mahone faces Daniel Netto in a heavyweight bout
next Monday at the Forum.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
