<HEADLINE>
IT'S ALL FALSE, EXILES SAY 
</HEADLINE>
  (Eds.: With CUBA-COMMANDO)  
(mk) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI _ The Cuban-American National Foundation on Sunday denied
a report in The New York Times that the group's late founder, Jorge
Mas Canosa, and other leaders financed the activities of Luis
Posada Carriles, who said he carried out a bombing campaign against
Cuba last year.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's all false and defamatory,'' a spokeswoman for the
foundation, Ninoska Perez, told Reuters.
</P>
<P>
   Last week, the foundation did not respond to telephone calls,
faxes and letters requesting interviews with its leaders to discuss
their relations with Posada. But in a statement faxed to The New
York Times on Friday, it denied financing his operations.
</P>
</TEXT>
